{"id":1268185042,"question_id":3444,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"2 weeks, 3 days","timestamp":1716699231,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"645 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1268185042/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find the Number of Good Pairs II","memory":"65.9 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public long numberOfPairs(int[] nums1, int[] nums2, int k) {\n        Map<Integer, Integer> nm = new HashMap<>();\n        for(int i : nums2)\n        {\n            int val = i * k;\n            nm.put(val, nm.getOrDefault(val, 0) + 1);\n        }\n        long ans=0;\n        for(int i : nums1)\n        {\n            for(int j=1;j*j<=i;j++)\n            {\n                if(i%j==0)\n                {\n                    if(nm.containsKey(j))\n                    {\n                        ans += nm.get(j);\n                    }\n                    int val=i/j;\n                    if(j!=val && nm.containsKey(val))\n                    {\n                        ans += nm.get(val);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        return ans;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"find-the-number-of-good-pairs-ii","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
